## ccrotate — Auto-rotate on rate limit

When you see ANY of these messages in the conversation:
- "You've hit your session limit"
- "You've hit your weekly limit"
- "You're now using extra usage"
- "You're out of extra usage"

Do this IMMEDIATELY without waiting for user input:
1. Run `ccrotate next` to find a base-tier account and switch (no restart needed — credentials are picked up automatically)
2. If `ccrotate next` switches successfully → tell the user and continue work
3. If ALL accounts are exhausted → run `ccrotate next --wait` which:
   - Switches to the earliest-reset account NOW (credentials on disk for when it resets)
   - Outputs JSON with `resetEpoch` (unix seconds)
   - Parse the `resetEpoch`, compute `delaySeconds = resetEpoch - now + 120` (2min buffer)
   - Use `ScheduleWakeup` with that delay and prompt: "Rate limit should have reset. Continue previous work."
4. Tell the user which account was selected and when it resets
<!-- CCROTATE:END -->
